.TH "fbtft_probe_common" 9 "fbtft_probe_common" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
fbtft_probe_common \- Generic device probe() helper function
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" fbtft_probe_common
.BI "(struct fbtft_display *display "  ","
.BI "struct spi_device *sdev "  ","
.BI "struct platform_device *pdev "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "display" 12
Display properties
.IP "sdev" 12
SPI device
.IP "pdev" 12
Platform device
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Allocates, initializes and registers a framebuffer

Either \fIsdev\fP or \fIpdev\fP should be NULL
.SH "RETURN"
0 if successful, negative if error
